React Router
1.	Add a js file separate named AppRoute.js
2.	Install;l react-router-dom  -- command -> npm i react-router-dom
3.	Import all the pages that you need to navigate
4.	Import Route, Switch from  react router using -> import { Route, Switch, NavLink, Link } from "react-router"; and also like this code
return (
      <Fragment>
        <Switch>
          <Route exact path="/" component={Home}></Route>
          <Route exact path="/contact" component={Contact}></Route>
        </Switch>
      </Fragment>
    );
5.	Also you need to navigate the pages from components.
6.	For this you need to import -> import { Route, Switch, NavLink, Link } from "react-router-dom";
7.	Use link as ->  <NavLink to="/">Back to home</NavLink>
8.	Also in the app js where the router component will placed import there browser router from react router dom.
9.	Then placed approytter.js  component
